# Leash — Robot Harness

## Product

A Rust harness runtime for robot control. DimOS-inspired parity surface built Rust-first, MCP-first, simulation-safe. LLM agents command physical robots through pilot-token-authorized sessions routed through a shared CapabilityRegistry with safety policy gates. Feature-gated hardware adapters (Waveshare UGV, MAVLink drone, manipulator arm). Safety classes: observe-only, sim-control, physical-stop, physical-motion, physical-high-risk. Blueprint catalog with `leash list` + `leash run`. Sim-safe by default — zero hardware required.

**Product benchmark**: `dimensionalOS/dimos` (3.5k stars, Python). Leash targets the same operating surface in Rust.

## Current State

| Entity | State | Ref |
|--------|-------|-----|
| Harness | stabilized | sim+physical drivers, safety gates, telemetry |
| CLI | implemented | serve mcp\|http, health, stop |
| MCPServer | implemented | 7 tools via rmcp |
| UGVAdapter | feature_gated | waveshare-ugv |
| Safety | implemented | deadman, estop, soft-odometry, smoke scripts |
| Bootstrap | bootstrapped | crate, license, CI (not yet green) |
| Telemetry | implemented | broadcast, WS streaming |
| ReleasePipeline | configured | Cargo.toml metadata |

## What the User Sees

### CLI: serve

```
$ leash serve mcp
[leash] profile: sim, role: robot
[leash] safety: deadman(400ms), estop, odometry-limit(0.0m), physical-gate(off)
[leash] MCP stdio ready (7 tools)

$ leash serve http --listen 127.0.0.1:8000
[leash] HTTP server on 127.0.0.1:8000 (16 endpoints + WS)
```

### CLI: daemon (planned)

```
$ leash run --daemon sim-http
[leash] daemon started (pid 18432), log: ~/.local/state/leash/sim-http.log
$ leash status
$ leash log sim-http
$ leash stop sim-http
```

### CLI: blueprints (planned)

```
$ leash list
sim-http     sim     http      no-hardware    Sim HTTP harness
sim-mcp      sim     mcp       no-hardware    Sim MCP harness
compat-http  sim     http      no-hardware    Bridge compatibility demo
waveshare-ugv  physical  http  waveshare-ugv  Waveshare UGV (HARDWARE)
```

### MCP (LLM Agent)

```
Tool: health, capabilities, observe, invoke_capability, stop, estop, capture
Planned: patrol_start, patrol_stop, memory_tag, memory_query, nav_set_goal, nav_cancel
```

### HTTP REST

```
GET  /health, /capabilities, /telemetry, /sensors, /camera/status, /stream
POST /capture, /pilot/authorize, /pilot/speed-mode, /drive, /motors/stop, /estop, /estop/reset
WS   /ws/telemetry
Planned: /agent/send, /capabilities/list, /policy/check
```

